# Privacy Policy - Dead Frontier

**Last Updated**: June 25, 2026

## Introduction

Studio ("we", "our", or "us") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting it through our compliance with this privacy policy. This policy describes how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our mobile game "Dead Frontier" (the "App").

## Information We Collect

### 1. Information Automatically Collected
When you use the App, we may automatically collect certain information, including:
- **Device Information**: Device model, operating system version, unique device identifiers
- **App Usage Data**: Game progress, achievements, in-game statistics, gameplay preferences
- **Performance Data**: Crash reports, performance metrics to improve app stability

### 2. Information Collected by Third Parties
The App uses third-party services that may collect information:

**Google AdMob (Advertising)**
- We use Google AdMob to display advertisements within the App
- Google may collect information about your device, location (approximate based on IP address), and app usage to serve relevant ads
- Google's use of advertising cookies and other tracking technologies is subject to Google's privacy policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy

**Google Analytics for Firebase**
- We may use Firebase Analytics to understand how users interact with the App
- This helps us improve the game experience and fix bugs
- Firebase collects anonymous usage data and crash reports

## How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information for the following purposes:

- **To Provide and Improve the App**: Maintain game functionality, fix bugs, and improve performance
- **To Personalize Ads**: Serve relevant advertisements based on your interests (via AdMob)
- **To Analyze Usage**: Understand player behavior to improve game design and features
- **To Ensure Security**: Detect fraud, abuse, and security threats

## Data Storage and Security

- Your game progress is stored locally on your device
- We do not store personal information on our servers
- We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information
- However, no method of transmission over the Internet is 100% secure

## Third-Party Services and Links

The App may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third parties. We encourage you to read the privacy policies of any third-party services you access.

### Third-Party Privacy Policies

- **Google (AdMob & Firebase)**: https://policies.google.com/privacy
- **Google Ads**: https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads

## Permissions Required

The App requests the following permissions:

- **INTERNET**: Required to load advertisements and enable analytics
- **ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE**: Required to check internet connectivity for ads
- **com.google.android.gms.permission.AD_ID**: Required by AdMob for ad personalization

## Children's Privacy

The App is not directed to children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete such information.

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new privacy policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date.

You are advised to review this privacy policy periodically for any changes.

